json 

Simple

{"key":"value","key_next":"value_next"}

Nested:

one value can have the same structure inside:

see below example

{"key" : "value" , "key_next": {"intenal_key" : "internal_value"} }

now if you have mutiple values than the nested values:

{"key" : "value" , "key_next": [{"intenal_key1" : "internal_value1"}, {"intenal_key2" : "internal_value2"} ] }

We can have multiple values in array without key pairs
  "operatingsystemrelease": [
        "5",
        "6",
        "7"
      ]


Everything is in double quote: 
Multiple values are in array
nested and arrays can be combined
We can use true and false without quotes in values.

